         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">[Promises of a large number of exhibits for the Manufacturers' Exhibition ¶ One of a number of exhibitions displaying local products that were mounted in Melbourne's splendid Exhibition Building, cons...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.03.00a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Exhibition Trustees, Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from a report of the meeting of the Exhibition Trustees held on 4 March 1884 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg>, 8 March 1884, p. 28).</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Promises of a large number of exhibits for the Manufacturers' Exhibition</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One of a number of exhibitions displaying local products that were mounted in Melbourne's splendid Exhibition Building, constructed for the International Exhibition, 1880-1, but now vacant. See the call for entries in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg> (Melbourne), 23 February 1884, p. 9.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> were reported, and letters were received from Baron von Mueller and Mr. Brough Smyth, agreeing to give the trustees their assistance in the formation of botanic and aboriginal collections</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In addition to temporary exhibits, it was proposed to mount some permanent displays.</p>
               </note>]</p>
         </div>
      </body>
